# ImageGenDemoSystem

## Purpose
SandboxApp text-to-image demo. Returns early until the input state exists, then lazily creates its
state singleton. While idle (no request issued yet), when the G key is pressed it emits a single
GenerateImageRequest for the resident checkpoint with a LoRA (`k_DiffusionLoraID`, weight 0.8) and an
OpenPose ControlNet hint (the loaded `k_DiffusionSkeletonID`), targeting `k_GeneratedTextureID` — the
UUID SceneSetupSystem's display sprite samples. Issues one request per session (generation is
expensive), latched by the state singleton's `m_Requested` flag.

## Input Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| InputStateSingletonComponent | read | G keypress triggers the request |

## Output Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| ImageGenDemoStateSingletonComponent | write / add (deferred) | Created once; `m_Requested` latches the single per-session request |
| GenerateImageRequestOneFrameComponent | add (oneframe) | The text-to-image request (engine-typed), read by the engine DiffusionSystem |
